{"questionId":"9074961","questionHtml":"<p>The energy density of a substance can be calculated by multiplying its specific energy with&nbsp;which quantity?</p>\n<p>A. mass</p>\n<p>B. volume</p>\n<p>C. <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{mass}}}}{{{\\text{volume}}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>mass</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>volume</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>D. <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{volume}}}}{{{\\text{mass}}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>volume</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>mass</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>C</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9074961","referenceCode":"17N.1.SL.TZ0.27","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"The energy density of a substance can be calculated by multiplying its specific energy with which quantity? A. mass B. volume C. mass volume D. volume mass","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"27","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 8: Energy production","8.1 – Energy sources","Core","Topic 8: Energy production"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}